# Atelier environment variables
#
# Optional. With nothing set, the site runs fully — the builder is open
# to everyone and the design brief is parsed on-device.

# --- AI brief parsing (Anthropic) -------------------------------------------
# Set this to have the builder parse the design brief with Claude.
# Without it, the brief is parsed on-device. Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Database & accounts (Supabase) -----------------------------------------
# Connect a Supabase project to persist projects/leads and enable sign-in.
# Find these under Supabase → Project Settings → API Keys. Both the new
# (sb_publishable_… / sb_secret_…) and legacy (anon / service-role) key
# formats are accepted. Without these, the app runs fully but data is not
# persisted and accounts are disabled.
#
# Public — safe to expose to the browser:
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#
# Server-only — bypasses row-level security. NEVER expose to the client and
# never paste into a NEXT_PUBLIC_ variable.
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=

# --- Deposit payments (Stripe) ----------------------------------------------
# Enables the client portal to collect a real design deposit via Stripe
# Checkout. Without these set, the portal runs a non-charging demo flow.
# Use test-mode keys (sk_test_… / whsec_…) while developing.
# Server-side only — never expose the secret key to the client.
#
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET comes from the webhook endpoint you create in the
# Stripe dashboard (Developers → Webhooks), pointed at /api/stripe-webhook
# and subscribed to the `checkout.session.completed` event.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
